file 1B desc text: Full websites dedicated to airing grievances for Chase QP unjustified acct closureclosures
file 1C desc text: 2020-01-09 LG writes email to Supporting Strategies Accounting statting Chase account closed due to fraud
file 1D desc text: 2020-01-10 RBC customer Tom Labadie uses chase online bill pay incorrectly endorsed and account is frozen
file 1E desc text: 2020-01-02 JZ explains Chase online billpay issue LG gets upset after JZ follows instructions
notes 1D:
2019-11-26 Tom Labadie used chase online bill pay to send five checks to RBC to close out open invoices.

On 2020-01-02 the check is returned showing TL accidentally had himself as payer and payee on the online generated checks.

2020-01-02 01:15 PM

JZ and TL (both Chase customers) contact the bank.

JZ is told to come into the Barry Plaza location on 3033 N. Pulaski with the checks.

TL goes to his branch cancels the 5 checks in person.

JZ is told by a teller to endorse the back of the the check.

JZ endorses one check and teller accepts.

The teller goes in the back while JZ endorses the rest of the checks.

A new teller comes out and tells JZ they now will not take checks that he endorsed despite JZ just following instructions.

TL while at his Chase branch messages:

1/2/20 1:26:10 PM

"Do u have checks? They said you can try to endorse on back."

1/2/20 1:29:03 PM

"Pay to order of rowboat creative account number and signature"

JZ responds he was told same thing and now the checks will not be accepted.

TL leaves his Chase branch and comes to the Barry Plaza branch to join JZ to try to sort out issue.

RBC was flagged for fraud despite TL apologizing for mistake.

2020-01-02 03:31 PM

TL sends $4288.63 via Zelle/Chase Quickpay with the intention of sending another $2269.32 the next morning.

At this point TL has now paid to cancel each check and has been on the phone as well as in person at his branch and then drives across the city to meet JZ at the Barry Plaza branch. This was not Tom's fault. He was gracious about the situation and very apologetic.

2020-01-10 09:57 AM

TL tries to send another payment via Zelle but receives error code 522208.

JZ replies "they cut off our quick pay"
